      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ARTISTRY IN MOTION (1) resumed in good order as the race favourite here in this grade, beaten 1.5L on the Scarpside here. Noske replaces the apprentice hoop today and he gets the blinkers on for the first time second-up. He is a second-up winner in the past and he can land the knockout blow this time. BONDI STAR (6) led them up in a change of tactics last time out and was too strong from the front, winning by 1L. Suspect she'll adopt similar tactics from the inside barrier today with Nottle again on board. Third-up now and can make an impression. JAZALOT (4) is hard to knock on his recent form, finishing 1.1L away last start after scoring a CL1 victory two back. This looks to shape favourably today and another forward showing is on the cards. PRINCE EPAULETTE (5) is better than he showed last time out when getting further back than anticipated in the run. Can return to form. HOWDY (2) is better than he showed last time out and can bounce back.",
